[Event "Sicilian Najdorf: Introduction"]
[Result "*"]

{The Najdorf Sicilian is the most popular and deeply analysed chess opening. Named after Miguel Najdorf, it has been the weapon of choice for Fischer, Kasparov, and countless world champions.} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 {The Najdorf Variation. Black's flexible move prepares ...e5 or ...b5 while keeping options open.} 6. Bg5 {The main line — White pins the knight and pressures d6.} (6. Be2 {The quiet positional approach.} e5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. Be3 {A slower but solid system.}) (6. Be3 {The English Attack — one of the most dangerous weapons against the Najdorf.} e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. f3 Be7 9. Qd2 O-O 10. O-O-O {Both sides castle opposite and attack on their respective flanks.}) (6. f3 {The line that leads to the English Attack setup.} e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. Be3 Be7 9. Qd2 O-O 10. O-O-O) e6 {The solid main line. Black closes the diagonal.} (6... e5 {Aggressive but weakens d5.} 7. Nf5 {White exploits the d5 weakness.}) 7. f4 {The Poisoned Pawn line begins.} Be7 (7... Qb6 {The famous Poisoned Pawn Variation!} 8. Qd2 Qxb2 9. Rb1 Qa3 {Extremely sharp and deeply theoretical.}) 8. Qf3 Qc7 9. O-O-O Nbd7 {Both sides are fully developed. A complex middlegame lies ahead.} *
